sentences: Robert Donnachie (1952–2000), known under the stage name of Robert Rental, was a British pioneer of the post-punk DIY industrial electronic music scene in the United Kingdom.
The only commercially-released solo recording from the 1970s is the 7-inch single "Paralysis" first released on the homemade Regular Records, then re-released on Company Records in 1978.
